                        <p style="margin: .2em 0 1em 2em;font-size: 90%;color: #454242 !important;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://org2.salsalabs.com/dia/track.jsp?v=2&c=2EbIjan3z1U5z8scTVl4VSRheDoyZ26M" style="text-decoration: none; color: #910000"><strong>Read the Article</strong></a>&#160;</p>
                        <p style="margin: 0 0 0.2em;font-size: 110%;color: #454242 !important;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://org2.salsalabs.com/dia/track.jsp?v=2&c=sPAIgmj%2F%2BuWJNJq5Koq7zCRheDoyZ26M" style="text-decoration: none; color: #570000"><strong>William Rivers Pitt | Within Reach of Your Arm</strong></a></p>
                        <p style="margin: 0;padding: 0;font-size: 100%;color: #444 !important;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;line-height: 1.1"><strong>William Rivers Pitt, Truthout:</strong>&#160;"All I have, all you have, all we have, is the power to do good and right within reach of our arm. I can't defeat ISIS, or suck the oil out of the Gulf. But I can do the best I can within reach of my arm, one reach at a time."</p>
