                        <p style="margin: 0 0 0.2em;font-size: 110%;color: #454242 !important;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://org2.salsalabs.com/dia/track.jsp?v=2&c=tTotKeSPgbYoPMENlx1SqyRheDoyZ26M" style="text-decoration: none; color: #570000"><strong>Is There Still Hope for Peace in Ukraine?</strong></a></p>
                        <p style="margin: 0;padding: 0;font-size: 100%;color: #444 !important;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;line-height: 1.1"><strong>Patrick Boylan, Pressenza:</strong>&#160;The Ukrainian government relentlessly goes on bombing residential areas in the eastern regions. The separatists are in a siege; to break it, they have launched a bloody counteroffensive. Yet, in spite of it all, a glimmer of hope for peace has appeared.</p>
