                        <p style="margin: 0 0 0.2em;font-size: 110%;color: #454242 !important;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://org2.salsalabs.com/dia/track.jsp?v=2&c=270qACdLY4OpgkxDds6s4iRheDoyZ26M" style="text-decoration: none; color: #570000"><strong>What "Battlestar Galactica" Can Teach Us About the Militarization of Police</strong></a></p>
                        <p style="margin: 0;padding: 0;font-size: 100%;color: #444 !important;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;line-height: 1.1"><strong>Christopher Zumski Finke, YES! Magazine:</strong>&#160;"There's a reason you separate the military and the police. One fights the enemy of the state, the other serves and protects the people. When the military becomes both, then the enemies of the state tend to become the people," says the "Battlestar Galactica" character Commander William Adama.</p>
                        <p style="margin: .2em 0 1em 2em;font-size: 90%;color: #454242 !important;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://org2.salsalabs.com/dia/track.jsp?v=2&c=oVbqQqRIutJRvDGszKHGUiRheDoyZ26M" style="text-decoration: none; color: #910000"><strong>Read the Article</strong></a>&#160;</p>
                        <p style="margin: 0 0 0.2em;font-size: 110%;color: #454242 !important;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://org2.salsalabs.com/dia/track.jsp?v=2&c=ynXtAEho41gsskyXpPRl3yRheDoyZ26M" style="text-decoration: none; color: #570000"><strong>Global Expansion of Fossil Fuel Transport, Drilling Underway as UN Climate Summit Approaches</strong></a></p>
                        <p style="margin: 0;padding: 0;font-size: 100%;color: #444 !important;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;line-height: 1.1"><strong>Sharmini Peries, The Real News Network:</strong>&#160;Environmental and humanities scholar and activist Subhankar Banerjee says we shouldn't expect much from global leaders gathering in New York City for the 2014 climate summit - most of their countries work with the fossil fuel industry.</p>
